{
  "stem": "13079.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "None to this extent that we tried these accused for violation of the laws and usages of war and for violations of laws that were just as valid as our criminal law, the criminal laws of Germany.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in Nuremberg waging aggressive warfare was a new offense.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I tried them-- the accused that I prosecuted-- for violation of the Geneva and Hague Conventions.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They had been in effect since 1907 and 1929, long before there was ever a Nazi Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So there was nothing ex post facto about the trials that I conducted and prosecuted there at Dachau.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What was done there in Dachau did not have the blessings of prior conduct that had been approved by humanity in general, if you please.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was in violation of written statutes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And those statutes were as much a part of the laws of Germany as they were a part of the laws of the United States.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That wasn't true in Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] [INAUDIBLE]",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Crimes against humanity-- that's a new one.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't use crimes against humanity.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't have to.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean all four.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had two rooms.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] They have two courtrooms there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And later on they had even more than that because when they started with the subsequent proceedings where they would introduce the findings of the court on the cases that I prosecuted, casting the burden of going forward with proof on those people who were then in the docks, that was not ex post facto, that was casting the burden of going forward to explain away what they did when they were there at Dachau, at [?",
      "word_count": 77
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Mauthausen, ?] at Flossenburg, and Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's correct.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Were at Dachau.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's correct.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was kind of sparse, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
